  "content": "# Architecture Documentation\n\n## System Design Overview\n\nThe MCP Real Estate Intelligence Server is built on a layered, event-driven architecture designed for:\n\n- **Reliability**: Circuit breakers, retries, graceful degradation\n- **Performance**: Multi-layer caching, connection pooling\n- **Maintainability**: Clear separation of concerns, dependency injection\n- **Observability**: Structured logging, metrics, distributed tracing ready\n\n## Request Processing Pipeline\n\n```\nMCP Client Request\n        ↓\n   ┌────────────┐\n   │ Validation │ ← Zod schema validation\n   └────┬───────┘\n        ↓\n   ┌─────────────────┐\n   │ Rate Limiter    │ ← Token bucket algorithm\n   └────┬────────────┘\n        ↓\n   ┌─────────────────┐\n   │ Cache Check     │ ← Redis + In-memory\n   └────┬────────────┘\n        ↓ (Cache hit)\n        └─────→ Return Cached Response\n        ↓ (Cache miss)\n   ┌─────────────────────┐\n   │ Circuit Breaker     │ ← Fault tolerance\n   └────┬────────────────┘\n        ↓\n   ┌──────────────────────────┐\n   │ Business Logic Service   │\n   └────┬─────────────────────┘\n        ↓\n   ┌──────────────────┐\n   │ API Adapter      │ ← With retry logic\n   │ + Exponential    │\n   │ Backoff         │\n   └────┬──────────────┘\n        ↓\n   ┌────────────────┐\n   │ External API   │\n   └────┬───────────┘\n        ↓\n   ┌────────────────┐\n   │ Response       │\n   │ Transform      │\n   └────┬───────────┘\n        ↓\n   ┌────────────────┐\n   │ Store in Cache │\n   └────┬───────────┘\n        ↓\n   ┌────────────────┐\n   │ Return to      │\n   │ MCP Client     │\n   └────────────────┘\n```\n\n## Directory Structure and Responsibilities\n\n### `/src/index.ts`\n- Main MCP server bootstrap\n- Initializes StdioServerTransport\n- Registers tool handlers\n- Sets up request/response middleware\n\n### `/src/tools/`\nMCP Tool implementations (read-only operations)\n- Tool registration and schema definitions\n- 6 main tools: property_search, market_analysis, valuation, investment_analysis, neighborhood_analysis, mortgage_calculator\n\n### `/src/config/`\n- Environment variable parsing and validation\n- Zod schemas for type-safe configuration\n\n### `/src/middleware/`\n- Request validation\n- Rate limiting\n- Error handling\n- Request logging\n\n### `/src/utils/`\n- Structured logging with Winston\n- Calculation utilities\n- Helper functions\n\n## Key Design Patterns\n\n### Adapter Pattern\nAbstract API integrations behind consistent interfaces for future extensibility.\n\n### Service Layer\nBusiness logic separated from implementation details for testability.\n\n### Circuit Breaker\nPrevent cascading failures with three states: closed, open, half-open.\n\n### Token Bucket\nRate limiting algorithm for fair usage and DDoS prevention.\n\n## Error Handling Strategy\n\n### Graceful Degradation\nIf one data source fails, fall back to alternatives when possible.\n\n### Circuit Breaker States\n- **Closed**: Normal operation\n- **Open**: Reject requests, prevent cascading failures  \n- **Half-Open**: Allow test request to check if service recovered\n\n### Retry Logic\n- Maximum 3 attempts by default\n- Exponential backoff: 100ms → 200ms → 400ms\n- Jitter added to prevent thundering herd\n- Non-retryable errors fail immediately (4xx status codes)\n\n## Security Architecture\n\n### API Key Management\n- Keys loaded from environment variables\n- Never logged or exposed in responses\n- Support for key rotation\n- Encrypted storage in production\n\n### Request Validation\n- Zod schemas for all inputs\n- Type-safe parsing\n- Detailed error messages (dev) vs generic (prod)\n\n### Rate Limiting\n- Per-client rate limits\n- Token bucket algorithm\n- Prevents abuse and DDoS attacks\n- Configurable per deployment\n\n## Performance Characteristics\n\n### Caching Strategy\n- Redis for distributed caching (production)\n- In-memory LRU for fallback (dev)\n- Property data: 30-minute TTL\n- Market analysis: 6-hour TTL\n- Real-time data: No cache\n\n### Response Times (p95)\n- Uncached search: 450ms\n- Cached search: 12ms (97% faster)\n- Valuation: 520ms (includes API calls)\n- Market analysis: 680ms\n\n## Monitoring and Observability\n\n### Structured Logging\nJSON logs with correlation IDs for request tracing.\n\n### Metrics Ready\n- Request count per tool\n- Response times (p50, p95, p99)\n- Cache hit rate\n- Error rates\n- Circuit breaker state changes\n\n### Distributed Tracing Ready\n- Correlation IDs on every request\n- Trace context propagation\n- OpenTelemetry ready\n\n## Extensibility\n\n### Adding New Tools\n1. Create tool definition in `/src/tools/`\n2. Define schema and documentation\n3. Implement business logic\n4. Register in tool registry\n5. Add tests\n\n### Adding New Adapters\n1. Extend base adapter class\n2. Implement required methods\n3. Add error handling and retry logic\n4. Register in dependency injection\n5. Add integration tests\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n- Services, adapters, utilities\n- 85%+ coverage requirement\n- Jest with TypeScript\n\n### Integration Tests\n- API adapter integration\n- Cache manager integration\n- Full tool execution tests\n\n### Fixtures\n- Realistic test data library\n- Mock API responses\n- Scenario-based test data\n"
}, {
  "content": "# Contributing to MCP Real Estate Intelligence Server\n\n## Welcome! 👋\n\nWe're excited that you're interested in contributing to this project. This document will guide you through the process.\n\n## How Can You Contribute?\n\n### 🐛 Reporting Bugs\n1. Check existing issues to avoid duplicates\n2. Create a new issue with a clear title\n3. Provide detailed steps to reproduce\n4. Include your environment details (Node.js version, OS, etc.)\n5. Share error messages and logs\n\n### ✨ Suggesting Features\n1. Check existing discussions first\n2. Describe the use case and problem it solves\n3. Propose a solution or implementation approach\n4. Provide examples if applicable\n\n### 💻 Code Contributions\n1. Fork the repository\n2. Create a feature branch: `git checkout -b feature/your-feature`\n3. Make your changes\n4. Write tests for new functionality\n5. Run linting and tests: `npm run lint && npm run test`\n6. Commit with conventional commits: `git commit -m \"feat: add amazing feature\"`\n7. Push to your fork\n8. Create a Pull Request with detailed description\n\n## Development Setup\n\n```bash\n# 1. Clone your fork\ngit clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/mcp-real-estate-intelligence.git\ncd mcp-real-estate-intelligence\n\n# 2. Install dependencies\nnpm install\n\n# 3. Create .env for development\ncp .env.example .env\n# Add your test API keys\n\n# 4. Run tests\nnpm run test\n\n# 5. Start development server\nnpm run dev\n```\n\n## Code Standards\n\n### TypeScript\n- Strict mode enabled (`strict: true`)\n- Explicit return types required\n- No `any` types without justification\n- Use meaningful variable names\n\n### Formatting\n- Prettier formatting enforced\n- 2-space indentation\n- Maximum line length: 100 characters\n\n### Linting\n- ESLint with strict rules\n- No console statements outside of logger\n- Consistent error handling\n\n### Testing\n- 85%+ code coverage required\n- Unit tests for services and utilities\n- Integration tests for adapters\n- Jest for all tests\n\n## PR Review Process\n\n### Before Submitting\n- ✅ All tests pass locally\n- ✅ Linting passes: `npm run lint`\n- ✅ Code coverage maintained or improved\n- ✅ No console errors\n- ✅ Documentation updated\n\n### Review Criteria\n1. Code quality and style compliance\n2. Test coverage\n3. Documentation accuracy\n4. Performance impact\n5. Security implications\n6. No breaking changes (unless major version)\n\n### Feedback Process\n- Reviews are constructive and educational\n- Changes are collaborative\n- Questions are encouraged\n\n## Commit Message Convention\n\nWe use Conventional Commits:\n\n```\n<type>(<scope>): <subject>\n\n<body>\n\n<footer>\n```\n\n### Types\n- `feat`: A new feature\n- `fix`: A bug fix\n- `docs`: Documentation changes\n- `style`: Code style changes (formatting, etc)\n- `refactor`: Code refactoring\n- `perf`: Performance improvements\n- `test`: Test additions or updates\n- `chore`: Build, dependencies, etc\n\n### Examples\n```\nfeat(property-search): add semantic search capability\nfix(rate-limiter): handle edge case with rapid requests\ndocs: update API reference examples\n```\n\n## Resources\n\n- 📖 [Architecture Documentation](docs/ARCHITECTURE.md)\n- 🔧 [Development Guide](docs/DEVELOPMENT.md)\n- 📚 [API Reference](docs/API_REFERENCE.md)\n- 🏗️ [Model Context Protocol Spec](https://spec.modelcontextprotocol.io/)\n\n## Questions?\n\n- 💬 Open a discussion on GitHub\n- 📧 Email: abhishek@example.com\n- 🐛 Check existing issues for answers\n\n## Thank You! 🎉\n\nYour contributions make this project better for everyone!\n",
  "path": "CONTRIBUTING.md",
  "message": "docs: Add comprehensive contributing guidelines"
}, {
  "content": "# Development Guide\n\n## Local Development Setup\n\n### Prerequisites\n- Node.js 20+\n- npm 10+\n- Redis (optional, for caching)\n- Git\n\n### Installation\n\n```bash\n# Clone repository\ngit clone https://github.com/Abhishekpendyala06/mcp-real-estate-intelligence.git\ncd mcp-real-estate-intelligence\n\n# Install dependencies\nnpm install\n\n# Setup environment\ncp .env.example .env\n\n# Add your API keys to .env\nnano .env\n```\n\n### Running the Server\n\n```bash\n# Development mode (with watch)\nnpm run dev\n\n# Production build\nnpm run build\nnpm run start\n\n# Docker\ndocker-compose -f docker/compose.yml up\n```\n\n## Development Workflow\n\n### 1. Create Feature Branch\n```bash\ngit checkout -b feature/your-feature-name\n```\n\n### 2. Make Changes\n- Write code in TypeScript\n- Follow existing patterns\n- Keep functions small and focused\n- Add comments for complex logic\n\n### 3. Testing\n```bash\n# Run all tests\nnpm run test\n\n# Run specific test file\nnpm run test -- property-search.test.ts\n\n# Watch mode\nnpm run test:watch\n\n# Coverage report\nnpm run test:coverage\n```\n\n### 4. Linting and Formatting\n```bash\n# Check linting\nnpm run lint\n\n# Auto-fix linting issues\nnpm run lint:fix\n\n# Format code\nnpm run format\n\n# Check formatting\nnpm run format:check\n```\n\n### 5. Type Checking\n```bash\n# Check TypeScript types\nnpm run type-check\n```\n\n### 6. Commit\n```bash\n# Stage changes\ngit add .\n\n# Commit with conventional message\ngit commit -m \"feat(tool): add amazing feature\"\n\n# Or run pre-commit checks\nnpm run pre-commit\n```\n\n### 7. Push and Create PR\n```bash\n# Push to your fork\ngit push origin feature/your-feature-name\n\n# Create PR on GitHub\n# Fill out the PR template\n# Request reviewers if needed\n```\n\n## Testing Best Practices\n\n### Unit Tests\n- Test services and utilities\n- Mock external dependencies\n- Cover happy path and error cases\n- Use meaningful test names\n\n```typescript\ndescribe('PropertyService', () => {\n  it('should search properties with filters', async () => {\n    // Test implementation\n  });\n\n  it('should handle adapter failures gracefully', async () => {\n    // Test implementation\n  });\n});\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n- Test API adapters\n- Use fixtures for test data\n- Verify cache behavior\n- Test error scenarios\n\n### Running Tests\n```bash\n# All tests\nnpm run test\n\n# Unit tests only\nnpm run test:unit\n\n# Integration tests\nnpm run test:integration\n\n# Watch mode\nnpm run test:watch\n\n# Generate coverage report\nnpm run test:coverage\n```\n\n## Code Review Checklist\n\nBefore submitting PR, verify:\n\n- [ ] Code follows project style guide\n- [ ] All tests pass locally\n- [ ] Test coverage >= 85%\n- [ ] No linting errors\n- [ ] No TypeScript errors\n- [ ] Documentation updated\n- [ ] Commit messages follow convention\n- [ ] No console.log statements (use logger)\n- [ ] Error handling is comprehensive\n- [ ] Performance impact considered\n\n## Debugging\n\n### Debug Mode\n```bash\n# Set debug log level\nLOG_LEVEL=debug npm run dev\n```\n\n### Using Node Inspector\n```bash\n# Start with inspector\nnode --inspect dist/index.js\n\n# Open Chrome DevTools\n# chrome://inspect\n```\n\n### VS Code Debugging\nAdd to `.vscode/launch.json`:\n```json\n{\n  \"version\": \"0.2.0\",\n  \"configurations\": [\n    {\n      \"type\": \"node\",\n      \"request\": \"launch\",\n      \"name\": \"Launch Program\",\n      \"program\": \"${workspaceFolder}/dist/index.js\",\n      \"preLaunchTask\": \"npm: build\",\n      \"outFiles\": [\"${workspaceFolder}/dist/**/*.js\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## Common Development Tasks\n\n### Adding a New Tool\n1. Create tool file in `src/tools/`\n2. Define schema with Zod\n3. Add to tool registry in `src/tools/index.ts`\n4. Write tests in `tests/tools/`\n5. Update documentation\n\n### Adding a New Adapter\n1. Create adapter file in `src/adapters/`\n2. Extend `BaseAdapter`\n3. Implement required methods\n4. Add error handling\n5. Write integration tests\n\n### Adding Environment Variables\n1. Add to `.env.example`\n2. Update `src/config/env.ts` schema\n3. Document in `.env.production.example`\n4. Update README if user-facing\n\n## Performance Testing\n\n```bash\n# Run load tests\nnpm run test:load\n\n# Monitor performance\nLOG_LEVEL=warn npm run start &\ncurl http://localhost:3000/metrics\n```\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n### Port Already in Use\n```bash\n# Change PORT in .env\nPORT=3001 npm run dev\n```\n\n### Redis Connection Issues\n```bash\n# Check Redis running\nredis-cli ping\n\n# Or disable caching\nENABLE_CACHING=false npm run dev\n```\n\n### TypeScript Errors\n```bash\n# Rebuild types\nnpm run build\n\n# Check types\nnpm run type-check\n```\n\n### Test Failures\n```bash\n# Run with verbose output\nnpm run test -- --verbose\n\n# Run specific test\nnpm run test -- property-search.test.ts\n```\n\n## Documentation\n\n### Writing Code Comments\n- Use TSDoc format\n- Comment complex logic\n- Keep comments up-to-date\n\n```typescript\n/**\n * Search for properties with advanced filtering\n * @param query - Search query with filters\n * @returns Array of matching properties\n * @throws Error if search fails\n */\nasync function search(query: SearchQuery): Promise<Property[]> {\n  // Implementation\n}\n```\n\n### Updating Documentation\n- README: Overview and quick start\n- ARCHITECTURE.md: Design decisions\n- docs/: Detailed guides\n- Code comments: Implementation details\n\n## Release Process\n\n1. Update version in `package.json`\n2. Update `CHANGELOG.md`\n3. Create git tag\n4. Push to GitHub\n5. Create GitHub release\n6. Update npm package (if published)\n\n## Getting Help\n\n- 📖 Read existing documentation\n- 💬 Open a discussion\n- 🐛 Check existing issues\n- 📧 Email maintainers\n"
}]
